Distribution : This species is a Southern Ocean species known predominately from the mesophotic, bathyal and abyssal depths of Antarctica ( Hentschel 1914 , Burton 1932 , 1934 , Koltun 1964 ,
Dressler-Allame et al. 2017
), Drakes Passage (
Goodwin et al. 2017
), Campos Basin, SE Brazil , SW Atlantic Ocean ( Lopes & Hajdu 2014 ), and now off Southern and central Eastern Australia , Tasman Sea, at abyssal depth.

Microscleres
: Anisochelae have three larger upper palmate alae with the two lateral alae fully attached to the fimbriae, and three smaller basal arcuate alae, partially or nearly fully fused together, and with serrations on the upper edges of the alae (
Table 15
) (
Figure 26 B
).
